content.text:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import qmc

# Create a 2D Sobol sequence
dim = 2
n_points = 1024
sobol_engine = qmc.Sobol(d=dim, scramble=False)
sobol_points = sobol_engine.random(n=n_points)

# Plot the Sobol sequence
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
plt.scatter(sobol_points[:, 0], sobol_points[:, 1], s=3, color='purple')
plt.title('Sobol Sequence (2D)')
plt.xlabel('Dimension 1')
plt.ylabel('Dimension 2')
plt.grid(True)
plt.axis('square')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
